&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Ward 25 ( General Surgery) - Part/full time - Internal rotation night / day duty&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Do you need a change? Would you like a challenge?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen on our busy 21 bedded Surgical Ward on the James Cook Site. We are looking for enthusiastic, highly motivated and dedicated experienced nurses to join our team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Ward 25 is a busy inpatient surgical ward specialising in Upper GI, Bariatric, and Gynaecology, Urology and Colorectal Surgery, we provide care for planned elective 14 day shielded patients.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We take great pride in our staff and we believe that investing in ‘You’ is key in our ability and capacity to deliver high quality service and patient care. We will support you in developing your surgical knowledge and skills through our team of supportive staff and formal education programme. You will work alongside Consultant Surgeons, Physiotherapists, Occupational Therapists and the wider multi-disciplinary team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Experience is not essential; however applicants must have a genuine interest in the speciality and be committed to delivering high quality patient care.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for enthusiastic, motivated people with effective communication skills.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A position with this directorate offers many opportunities for individuals to develop their clinical skills and ongoing professional development is encouraged and supported.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Ward Manager Anthea Davison or Sisters: Toni Labonte, Emma Todd or Amy Brown&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Tel: 01642 854525 / 856659&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
